4827SDValue
4828DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorExtLoads(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &LdChain,
4829 LoadSDNode *LD,
4830 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType) {
4831 // For extension loads, it may not be more efficient to chop up the vector
4832 // and then extend it. Instead, we unroll the load and build a new vector.
4833 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(),LD->getValueType(0));
4834 EVT LdVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
4835 SDLoc dl(LD);
4836 assert(LdVT.isVector() && WidenVT.isVector());
4837
4838 // Load information
4839 SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
4840 SDValue BasePtr = LD->getBasePtr();
4841 unsigned Align = LD->getAlignment();
4842 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
4843 AAMDNodes AAInfo = LD->getAAInfo();
4844
4845 EVT EltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
4846 EVT LdEltVT = LdVT.getVectorElementType();
4847 unsigned NumElts = LdVT.getVectorNumElements();
4848
4849 // Load each element and widen.
4850 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
4851 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts);
4852 unsigned Increment = LdEltVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
4853 Ops[0] =
4854 DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, EltVT, Chain, BasePtr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
4855 LdEltVT, Align, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
4856 LdChain.push_back(Ops[0].getValue(1));
4857 unsigned i = 0, Offset = Increment;
4858 for (i=1; i < NumElts; ++i, Offset += Increment) {
4859 SDValue NewBasePtr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, BasePtr, Offset);
4860 Ops[i] = DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, EltVT, Chain, NewBasePtr,
4861 LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset), LdEltVT,
4862 Align, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
4863 LdChain.push_back(Ops[i].getValue(1));
4864 }
4865
4866 // Fill the rest with undefs.
4867 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
4868 for (; i != WidenNumElts; ++i)
4869 Ops[i] = UndefVal;
4870
4871 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, dl, Ops);
4872}
4873
4874void DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorStores(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &StChain,
4875 StoreSDNode *ST) {
4876 // The strategy assumes that we can efficiently store power-of-two widths.
4877 // The routine chops the vector into the largest vector stores with the same
4878 // element type or scalar stores.
4879 SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
4880 SDValue BasePtr = ST->getBasePtr();
4881 unsigned Align = ST->getAlignment();
4882 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
4883 AAMDNodes AAInfo = ST->getAAInfo();
4884 SDValue ValOp = GetWidenedVector(ST->getValue());
4885 SDLoc dl(ST);
4886
4887 EVT StVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
4888 unsigned StWidth = StVT.getSizeInBits();
4889 EVT ValVT = ValOp.getValueType();
4890 unsigned ValWidth = ValVT.getSizeInBits();
4891 EVT ValEltVT = ValVT.getVectorElementType();
4892 unsigned ValEltWidth = ValEltVT.getSizeInBits();
4893 assert(StVT.getVectorElementType() == ValEltVT);
4894
4895 int Idx = 0; // current index to store
4896 unsigned Offset = 0; // offset from base to store
4897 while (StWidth != 0) {
4898 // Find the largest vector type we can store with.
4899 EVT NewVT = FindMemType(DAG, TLI, StWidth, ValVT);
4900 unsigned NewVTWidth = NewVT.getSizeInBits();
4901 unsigned Increment = NewVTWidth / 8;
4902 if (NewVT.isVector()) {
4903 unsigned NumVTElts = NewVT.getVectorNumElements();
4904 do {
4905 SDValue EOp = DAG.getNode(
4906 ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, NewVT, ValOp,
4907 DAG.getConstant(Idx, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
4908 StChain.push_back(DAG.getStore(
4909 Chain, dl, EOp, BasePtr, ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset),
4910 MinAlign(Align, Offset), MMOFlags, AAInfo));
4911 StWidth -= NewVTWidth;
4912 Offset += Increment;
4913 Idx += NumVTElts;
4914
4915 BasePtr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, BasePtr, Increment);
4916 } while (StWidth != 0 && StWidth >= NewVTWidth);
4917 } else {
4918 // Cast the vector to the scalar type we can store.
4919 unsigned NumElts = ValWidth / NewVTWidth;
4920 EVT NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewVT, NumElts);
4921 SDValue VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVecVT, ValOp);
4922 // Readjust index position based on new vector type.
4923 Idx = Idx * ValEltWidth / NewVTWidth;
4924 do {
4925 SDValue EOp = DAG.getNode(
4926 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, NewVT, VecOp,
4927 DAG.getConstant(Idx++, dl,
4928 TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
4929 StChain.push_back(DAG.getStore(
4930 Chain, dl, EOp, BasePtr, ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset),
4931 MinAlign(Align, Offset), MMOFlags, AAInfo));
4932 StWidth -= NewVTWidth;
4933 Offset += Increment;
4934 BasePtr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, BasePtr, Increment);
4935 } while (StWidth != 0 && StWidth >= NewVTWidth);
4936 // Restore index back to be relative to the original widen element type.
4937 Idx = Idx * NewVTWidth / ValEltWidth;
4938 }
4939 }
4940}

4942void
4943DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorTruncStores(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &StChain,
4944 StoreSDNode *ST) {
4945 // For extension loads, it may not be more efficient to truncate the vector
4946 // and then store it. Instead, we extract each element and then store it.
4947 SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
4948 SDValue BasePtr = ST->getBasePtr();
4949 unsigned Align = ST->getAlignment();
4950 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
4951 AAMDNodes AAInfo = ST->getAAInfo();
4952 SDValue ValOp = GetWidenedVector(ST->getValue());
4953 SDLoc dl(ST);
4954
4955 EVT StVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
4956 EVT ValVT = ValOp.getValueType();
4957
4958 // It must be true that the wide vector type is bigger than where we need to
4959 // store.
4960 assert(StVT.isVector() && ValOp.getValueType().isVector());
4961 assert(StVT.bitsLT(ValOp.getValueType()));
4962
4963 // For truncating stores, we can not play the tricks of chopping legal vector
4964 // types and bitcast it to the right type. Instead, we unroll the store.
4965 EVT StEltVT = StVT.getVectorElementType();
4966 EVT ValEltVT = ValVT.getVectorElementType();
4967 unsigned Increment = ValEltVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
4968 unsigned NumElts = StVT.getVectorNumElements();
4969 SDValue EOp = DAG.getNode(
4970 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, ValEltVT, ValOp,
4971 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
4972 StChain.push_back(DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl, EOp, BasePtr,
4973 ST->getPointerInfo(), StEltVT, Align,
4974 MMOFlags, AAInfo));
4975 unsigned Offset = Increment;
4976 for (unsigned i=1; i < NumElts; ++i, Offset += Increment) {
4977 SDValue NewBasePtr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, BasePtr, Offset);
4978 SDValue EOp = DAG.getNode(
4979 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, ValEltVT, ValOp,
4980 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
4981 StChain.push_back(DAG.getTruncStore(
4982 Chain, dl, EOp, NewBasePtr, ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset),
4983 StEltVT, MinAlign(Align, Offset), MMOFlags, AAInfo));
4984 }
4985}

4987/// Modifies a vector input (widen or narrows) to a vector of NVT. The
4988/// input vector must have the same element type as NVT.
4989/// FillWithZeroes specifies that the vector should be widened with zeroes.
4990SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ModifyToType(SDValue InOp, EVT NVT,
4991 bool FillWithZeroes) {
4992 // Note that InOp might have been widened so it might already have
4993 // the right width or it might need be narrowed.
4994 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
4995 assert(InVT.getVectorElementType() == NVT.getVectorElementType() &&
4996 "input and widen element type must match");
4997 SDLoc dl(InOp);
4998
4999 // Check if InOp already has the right width.
5000 if (InVT == NVT)
5001 return InOp;
5002
5003 unsigned InNumElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
5004 unsigned WidenNumElts = NVT.getVectorNumElements();
5005 if (WidenNumElts > InNumElts && WidenNumElts % InNumElts == 0) {
5006 unsigned NumConcat = WidenNumElts / InNumElts;
5007 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumConcat);
5008 SDValue FillVal = FillWithZeroes ? DAG.getConstant(0, dl, InVT) :
5009 DAG.getUNDEF(InVT);
5010 Ops[0] = InOp;
5011 for (unsigned i = 1; i != NumConcat; ++i)
5012 Ops[i] = FillVal;
5013
5014 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, NVT, Ops);
5015 }
5016
5017 if (WidenNumElts < InNumElts && InNumElts % WidenNumElts)
5018 return DAG.getNode(
5019 ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, NVT, InOp,
5020 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
5021
5022 // Fall back to extract and build.
5023 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts);
5024 EVT EltVT = NVT.getVectorElementType();
5025 unsigned MinNumElts = std::min(WidenNumElts, InNumElts);
5026 unsigned Idx;
5027 for (Idx = 0; Idx < MinNumElts; ++Idx)
5028 Ops[Idx] = DAG.getNode(
5029 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, InOp,
5030 DAG.getConstant(Idx, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
5031
5032 SDValue FillVal = FillWithZeroes ? DAG.getConstant(0, dl, EltVT) :
5033 DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
5034 for ( ; Idx < WidenNumElts; ++Idx)
5035 Ops[Idx] = FillVal;
5036 return DAG.getBuildVector(NVT, dl, Ops);
5037}
